2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 139
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS
A RESOLUTION
To recognize Wednesday, May 20, 2026, as "White Coat Wednesday" at the Louisiana State
Capitol.
WHEREAS, cities, towns, communities, and residents across the state of Louisiana
are proud of the state's physicians for their commitment, dedication, and personal sacrifice
as they strive to provide comprehensive and compassionate medical care to all Louisianians;
and
WHEREAS, society owes a debt of gratitude to physicians for their sympathy and
compassion in ministering to the sick and in alleviating human suffering; and
WHEREAS, society commends physicians for their contributions in enlarging the
reservoir of scientific knowledge, increasing the number of scientific tools, and expanding
the ability of healthcare professionals to use knowledge and tools effectively in the
never-ending fight against disease; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana physicians continue to play a vital and significant role in
caring for families and individuals; and
WHEREAS, White Coat days allow physicians to discuss healthcare issues with
legislators and relay the issues that affect their patients on a daily basis.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby recognize Wednesday, May 20, 2026, as "White Coat Wednesday" at the
Louisiana State Capitol.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Louisiana State Medical Society and the Louisiana Academy of Family Physicians.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
